steps.body:
You will need to do the following in order to set up WebGNOME for Mobile Bay :

  1. Set the model run parameters.
  2. Set the Mobile River flow rate.
  3. Input the wind conditions.
steps.name: Welcome to Mobile Bay

<style>.form-modal .option { 
   background: #efefef;
   height: 90px;
   margin-bottom: 20px;
   border-radius: 4px;
   cursor: pointer;
   overflow: hidden;
}

.form-modal .option:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 0;
}

.form-modal .option .icon {
    width: 90px;
   height: 90px;
   background: #428bca;
   float: left;
   background-position: center center;
   background-repeat: no-repeat;
}

.form-modal .option .title {
      font-size: 15px;
      padding: 15px 15px 10px 15px;
}

.form-modal .option p {
   padding-left: 15px;
   font-size: 11px;
}

.form-modal .option.relaxation .icon {
      background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);
}

.form-modal .option.upwelling .icon {
      background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);
}

.form-modal .option.convergent .icon {
      background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);
}</style><p> You can choose an estimate of the Mobile river flow or input stage height at the Barry Steam Plant. The stage height must be between 3 and 20 feet. </p> <p> The total flow of the Mobile River is primarily controlled by the amount of water flowing over dams upriver from the Barry Steam Plant. Stage heights at the steam plant can be used to estimate Mobile River flow. </p> <form class=form-horizontal role=form> <div class=form-group> <label class="col-sm-5 control-label" for=riverflow>Mobile River Flow:</label> <div class=col-sm-5> <select class=form-control id=riverflow> <option value=200> High 200 kcfs </option> <option value=80> Medium 80 kcfs </option> <option value=30> Low 30 kcfs </option> <option value=other> I'll specify stage height </option> </select> </div> </div> <div class="form-group height hide"> <label class="col-sm-5 control-label" for=stageheight>Stage height:</label> <div class=col-sm-4> <input type=number id=stageheight class=form-control> </div> <div class=col-sm-3> <select class=form-control id=stageheight-units> <option value=ft> ft </option> <option value=m> m </option> </select> </div> </div> <div class="form-group height hide"> <div class="col-sm-7 col-sm-offset-5"> <a href=http://water.sam.usace.army.mil/barry.jpg target=_blank> Stage Height Information (in feet) </a> </div> </div> </form>

steps.body:
Wind can significantly influence oil movement and can force oil to move in a different direction from the currents.

You can choose wind that is constant in direction and speed for the entire model run, or you can choose wind that varies in direction and/or speed over time.
steps.title: Wind Type
